column47: "Melody is common to those of the Puyuma"
Call back the soul to this world
Usually sung by men at weddings
Originally sung by Ravals (north) later introduced to other Paiwan
Women's version of "song of brave warriors", professing chastity
Family sings to bride night before wedding
Sung by men at Bumper Harvest Year Festival (not same song as Paiwan "Song of Brave Warriors")
Formerly for hunter who killed 6 boars. Now that hunting forbidden, just general boasting song
Flirting ("Please give us some tea to drink. We are so tired. And would you be so kind to grant us some of your love?")
About head-hunting. Reminds Kurosawa and others of Buddhist chanting
